	test/data/echo/final/final.txt (tags: v_0_1_109, v_0_1_31, v_0_1_4,
	v_0_1_3, v_0_1_0_base), test/data/echo/final/template.txt (tags:
	v_0_1_109, v_0_1_31, v_0_1_4, v_0_1_3, v_0_1_0_base),
	test/data/echo/setup/template.txt (tags: v_0_1_109, v_0_1_31,
	v_0_1_4, v_0_1_3, v_0_1_0_base): Added an "input"
	attribute/property to the <echo> tast so it can be used to evaluate
	property instances in external templates:
	
	  <echo input="template.txt" file="output.txt" />
	
	Will evaluate all property instances ( ${propname}  ) in
	template.txt and write the result to output.txt./

