	blank lines at start of file.

2001-04-10 17:28  juanco

	* src/: WantClasses.pas, tasks/DelphiTasks.pas,
	tasks/WantTasks.pas, tasks/EchoTasks.pas, tasks/ExecTasks.pas,
	tasks/FileTasks.pas, tasks/ZipTasks.pas: Merged FileOps into
	WildPaths

2001-04-10 17:19  juanco

	* src/WantClasses.pas: BUG: Dante parses and builds did not restore
	the current directory. Fixed.

2001-04-09 20:38  chrismo

	* test/: DanteAcceptTest.dpr, ExternalTests.pas,
	data/move.final.zip, data/move.setup.zip, data/move.xml,
	data/unzip.exe (tags: added_color): Added external testing harness.
	There's a new directory off test called data. To add a new test,
	include 3 new files, all with the same root: root.xml,
	root.setup.zip, root.final.zip. DanteExternalTest (now executed in
	DanteAcceptTest.zip) will read in all .xml files in the data
	directory and create a TExternalTest instance for each.
	
	TExternalTest will setup a throwaway directory by extracting
	root.setup.zip and placing root.xml in the root folder where
	.setup.zip was extracted. Then it runs Dante with root.xml. Then
	.final.zip is extracted in a sibling directory and the contents of
	the setup and final folders are compared. If they match, the test
	passes. If they fail, the contents of both are displayed.
	
	Currently, only folder and file names are compared, contents of
	actual files are ignored.
	
	The first and only test in there now tests the move task (move.xml,
	move.setup.xml, move.final.xml). I wasn't sure if I could use zlib
	to extract these zips and keep directory structure intact, so
	InfoZip's unzip.exe is included and used for now.

2001-04-09 20:34  chrismo

	* test/RunnerTests.pas: Changed formatting on MainTest xml file

2001-04-09 16:19  chrismo

	* test/DanteTest.dpr: Added WildPathsTest to .dpr

2001-04-09 16:19  chrismo

	* test/RunnerTests.pas: Added check (currently failing) for current
	directory being changed. Something in the xml acceptance test is
	changing the current directory unnecessarily.

